{"cursor":"2800","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"{{Infobox Company\n| company_name = Gamelion company_logo = company_type = Privately Held Company\n| foundation = 2002 location = Helsinki, Finland key_people = industry = Game\n| Development, Mobile Game Development, Mobile Porting and Quality Assurance Casual Games products = 'Games:' FIFA 07, FIFA 08, Puzzle Bubble: Mobile\n| Mania, NitroSpin Racer, Stunt Racing 99 Tracks, LocoRoco Hi and more 'Own\n| IP:' Global Race - Raging Thunder, Global Cricket, Furry Legends (Wii) clients\n| = EA Mobile, Sony Pictures, Square Enix, Namco Bandai, Nokia, Qualcomm revenue\n| = Private net_income = Private num_employees = '100' (2009) parent = subsid =\n| homepage = [http://www.game-lion.com Gamelion Official Web Site] footnotes =\n}}\n\n'Gamelion' is an independent award-winning developer of video games and\nentertainment applications for all mobile devices, handhelds and consoles. The\ncompany was founded 2002 in Finland and received in 2005 venture capital from\n[http://www.magnoliaventures.com Magnolia Ventures]. The main development studio\nis located in Szczecin, Poland. A second studio was established in 2007 in\nBydgoszcz, Poland. In total, as of February 2009, Gamelion Studios has around\n100 employees.\n\nOn August 2007 Gamelion announced a merger with [http://www.blstream.com\nBLStream Ltd]. [http://www.bellstream.com/cNews5.html Blstream Group ] Together with Gamelion the group now employs\nover 250 people.\n\nIn 2008 Gamelion has been authorized by Nintendo for development on Nintendo\nWii, Nintendo DS and by Sony for PlayStation Portable.\n\nOn January 30, 2009 Gamelion announced [http://www.furrylegends.com Furry\nLegends] their ongoing development of first game for WiiWare service, scheduled\nfor launch in summer 2009. After several delays the game has been released in\nUnited States on July 19th, 2010.\n","linknr":103,"url":"Gamelion_Studios","recorded":1375081558,"links":["/w/index.php?title=